      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PARUMBA JAZZMAN (2) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (26.00) at this track over 460m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Rates highly and will give a great sight. HARD TO ROCK (4) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (26.26) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Likely to be about the mark. MYSTERY NELL (1) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling off pace at Healesville, but prior to that won by half a length at Healesville (19.46) beating Especial Kiani in a T3 RSTW on June 12. Expected to feature in the finish. HI BIG BEN (7) is a last-start placegetter worth considering.",
